;SEQUENCE ADVISORY NOTICE:
     DIFFERENCE BETWEEN SWISS-PROT AND PDB SEQUENCE.

     SWISS-PROT ENTRY NAME: PER_COPCI

     SWISS-PROT RESIDUE      PDB SEQRES
       NAME   NUMBER         NAME  CHAIN  SEQ/INSERT CODE
        -                    GLY            4
       VAL    100            ILE          100

THERE ARE TWO VARIANTS VAL/ILE AT THIS POSITION AND VAL
VARIANT PREDOMINATES.
THE AUTHORS' SEQUENCING RESULTS FOR ARP ARE CONSISTENT
WITH THOSE FROM COPRINUS PEROXIDASE REPORTED BY
BAUNSGAARD ET AL. (1993) EXCEPT THAT ARP HAS AN INSERTION
OF GLYCINE AT THE AMINO TERMINAL GLYCINE-RUCH REGION.
THEY REPORTED THAT TWO VARIANTS ARE PRESENT IN COPRINUS
CINEREUS PEROXIDASE (VAL/ILE AT 99TH POSITION) AND THAT
THE VAL VARIANT PREDOMINATES.  THE AUTHORS' X-RAY ANALYSIS
SUGGESTS THAT THE CORRESPONDING POSITION IN ARP IS OCCUPIED
BY ILE; THE ELECTRON DENSITY FOR CD ILE 100 IS CLEAR IN THE
FINAL 2FO-FC MAP.
;
